**Segments**

The deflectable catheters market can be segmented based on product type, application, end-user, and geography. In terms of product type, the market can be categorized into uni-directional deflectable catheters and bi-directional deflectable catheters. The uni-directional deflectable catheters segment is expected to witness significant growth due to their precise navigation capabilities within the body. Application-wise, the market can be divided into cardiovascular procedures, neurovascular procedures, urology procedures, and others. Cardiovascular procedures hold a major share in the market owing to the rising prevalence of cardiovascular diseases globally. Based on end-user, the market segments include hospitals, ambulatory surgical centers, and specialty clinics. Hospitals are the largest end-users of deflectable catheters due to the high volume of surgical procedures performed in these settings. Geographically, the market is segmented into North America, Europe, Asia Pacific, Latin America, and the Middle East and Africa.

